  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Survivor-led livelihoods support in Rakhine - LPRR</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Both projects will strengthen the resilience of these conflict-affected communities, which will allow for further resilience to future emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MRF
Consultation with community for project design and beneficiary selection
Fish net making supplies and training for widows
Chicken husbandry training and supplies and educational support through teachers&apos; salaries
Post project/distribution monitoring

BBS
5 days training to the Bawdi Ahlinn Foundation and 25 survivor families
Joint consultation together with Bawdi Ahlinn Education Foundation to the 25 survivor families to find possibilities for livelihood setup
Capital investment support (350,000 MK per family)
Participatory monitoring and evaluation</narrative>
  </description>
